                    CALIFORNIA LEGISLATURE—
                    2025–2026 REGULAR SESSION</font></div><br clear="all"/><span id="bill_house_num"><div style="float: left; width:50%; font-weight: bold; "><span style="text-transform: uppercase; text-align:left;width:50%;"><b>
                Assembly Bill
              </b></span></div><div style="float:right; width:50%; text-align:right;"><span style="text-transform: uppercase;"><b>No. 1924</b></span></div></span><hr/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><table style="border-collapse: collapse" cellSpacing="0" align="center" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td id="bill_authors" align="center"><span style="font-weight:bold;">Introduced by Assembly Members Gabriel and Quirk-Silva<br/>(Coauthors: Assembly Members Caloza, Haney, and Kalra)<br/><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>(Coauthor: Senator Arreguín)<br/></i></font></span></td></tr><tr><td id="bill_intro_date" align="center" class="textcenter"><br/>February 12, 2026</td></tr></tbody></table></div><hr/><br clear="all"/><div id="title"><span style="font-weight:normal;font-size:0.9em;"> An act to add<font color="#B30000"><strike> Chapter 1.7 (commencing with Section 50430) to Part 2 of Division 31 of the Health and Safety</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> Section 8257.4 to the Welfare and Institutions</i></font> Code, relating to<font color="#B30000"><strike> housing.</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> homelessness.</i></font></span></div><br clear="all"/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><h2>LEGISLATIVE COUNSEL'S DIGEST</h2></div><br/><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0"><span id="subject">AB 1924, as amended, Gabriel.
                          Statewide homelessness prevention strategy.</span></div><div><span id="digesttext"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Existing law establishes the<font color="#B30000"><strike> Department of Housing and Community Development and requires the department to oversee and implement various housing programs.</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> California Interagency Council on Homelessness and requires the council to take various actions to prevent and end homelessness in California.</i></font> Existing law establishes various programs to prevent homelessness or assist persons experiencing homelessness, including the No Place Like Home Program and the Homeless Housing, Assistance, and Prevention program.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This bill would require the<font color="#B30000"><strike> department,</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>
			 council,</i></font> by July 1, 2027, to develop and publicly issue a statewide homelessness prevention strategy that includes specified elements, including a homelessness prevention action plan for certain state agencies and evidence-based model homeless prevention practices, as specified. The bill would require the<font color="#B30000"><strike> department</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> council</i></font> to annually review and update the strategy and publish any revisions. The bill would define various terms for these purposes.</div></span></div><span class="hidden"><h2>Digest Key</h2></span><span id="vote">
      Vote:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">MAJORITY</span>  </span><span id="appropriation">
      Appropriation:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span><span id="fiscalcommittee">
      Fiscal Committee:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">YES</span>  </span><span id="localprogram">
      Local Program:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span></div><hr/><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Text</h2></span><div id="bill"><div style=" text-transform: uppercase"><h2 style=" text-align: left;">The people of the State of California do enact as follows:</h2><br/></div><font color="#B30000"><strike><caml:BillSection id="id_BA290D7E-6571-434F-8C1D-B467635C224F"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>SECTION 1.</caml:Num><caml:ActionLine action="IS_ADDED" xlink:href="urn:caml:codes:WIC:caml#xpointer(%2Fcaml%3ALawDoc%2Fcaml%3ACode%2F%2Fcaml%3ALawSection%5Bcaml%3ANum%3D'8257.4'%5D)" xlink:label="fractionType: LAW_SECTION" xlink:type="locator">Chapter 1.7 (commencing with Section 50430)  is added to Part 2 of Division 31 of the <caml:DocName>Health and Safety Code</caml:DocName>,  to read:</caml:ActionLine>
			 <caml:Fragment>


				<caml:LawHeading id="id_A80B82F8-D286-43AA-9DED-E8DB2F418B87" type="CHAPTER">
				  <div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>1.7.</caml:Num><caml:LawHeadingVersion id="id_DBF8205C-9167-4D49-B152-E33E8F6B579F"><caml:LawHeadingText>Statewide Homelessness Prevention Strategy</caml:LawHeadingText></caml:LawHeadingVersion>
				  <caml:LawSection id="id_70B74EA1-2865-4A84-9B7D-EA261B1E6E8F">
<div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>50430.</caml:Num><caml:LawSectionVersion id="id_5F3A7ECC-03AE-48B1-ADA8-0A457D152688"><caml:Content/></caml:LawSectionVersion>
				  </caml:LawSection>
				</caml:LawHeading>

			 </caml:Fragment>
		  </caml:BillSection></strike></font><div id="s20.2900452577589744"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0" class="ActionLine"><h3 style="font-weight:bold; display:inline;"><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>SECTION 1.</i></font></h3> <font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>Section 8257.4 is added to the Welfare and Institutions Code, to read:</i></font></div><div><div id="id_805E6601-C07C-447E-9D39-12FE7A3DBD1A"><div><p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><h6 style="display:inline;"><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>8257.4.</i></font></h6> (a) For purposes of this<font color="#B30000"><strike> chapter:</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> section:</i></font></div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(1) “At risk of homelessness” means the presence of multiple evidence-based homelessness risk factors for an individual, including, but not limited to, any of the following:</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(A) Prior experience of homelessness.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(B) Annual income below 30
						percent of the area median income.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(C) Experiencing rent burden.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(D) Experiencing other household and social characteristics that are known to elevate the risk of homelessness.</div><font color="#B30000"><strike><s><p style="margin-left: 1em;">(2)<span class="EnSpace"/>“Department” means the Department of Housing and Community Development.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><s><p style="margin-left: 1em;">(3)</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(2)</i></font> “Homelessness prevention” or “preventing homelessness” means reducing the inflow of
						individuals into the population of people experiencing homelessness.</div><font color="#B30000"><strike><s><p style="margin-left: 1em;">(4)</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(3)</i></font> “Homeless prevention action plan” means a plan described in paragraph (4) of subdivision (b).</div><font color="#B30000"><strike><s><p style="margin-left: 1em;">(5)</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(4)</i></font> “Housing stability” means the ability of an individual or family to maintain housing that is consistent, safe,
						and affordable.</div><font color="#B30000"><strike><s><p style="margin-left: 1em;">(6)</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(5)</i></font> “Relevant agency” means any state agency or department that affects, or has the potential to affect, housing stability and the prevention of homelessness, including, but not limited to, all of the following:</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(A) The<font color="#B30000"><strike> department.</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>
						council.</i></font></div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(B) The<font color="#B30000"><strike> Interagency Council on Homelessness.</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> Department of Housing and Community Development.</i></font></div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(C) The State Department of Social Services.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(D) The Department of Corrections and Rehabilitation.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(E) The Division of Rehabilitative Programs, Department of Corrections and Rehabilitation.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(F) The Office of Youth and Community Restoration, California Health and Human Services Agency.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(G) The California Health and Human Services Agency.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(H) The State Department of Public Health.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(I) The State Department of Health Care Services.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(J) The State Department of State Hospitals.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(K) The Employment Development Department.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(L) The State Department of Education.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(b) By July 1, 2027, the<font color="#B30000"><strike> department</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> council</i></font> shall
						develop and publicly issue a statewide homelessness prevention strategy that includes, but is not limited to, all of the following:</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(1) The identity of each relevant agency.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(2) An inventory of each definition of homelessness prevention employed by each relevant agency and how those definitions differ.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(3) The actions each relevant agency is taking to promote housing stability and homelessness prevention and the gaps in those actions.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(4) (A) A homelessness prevention action plan for each relevant agency that is developed by the<font color="#B30000"><strike> department</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>
						council</i></font> and the relevant agency that details specific actions, in addition to those described in paragraph (3), the agency will take to contribute to housing stability and homelessness prevention and the timeline for those actions.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(B) Each homelessness prevention action plan developed pursuant to subparagraph (A) shall consider available model practices developed pursuant to paragraph (12) and relevant evidence-based research and practice regarding the prevention of homelessness.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(5) Recommendations for legislation or executive action to implement the homelessness prevention action plans.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(6) A plan to coordinate and integrate the homelessness prevention action plans.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(7) A plan to annually evaluate the effectiveness and efficiency of the homelessness prevention action plans that includes, but is not limited to, both of the following:</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(A) Accountability measures.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(B) An assessment of the impact of the homelessness prevention action plans on homelessness prevention.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(8) An inventory of state resources currently devoted specifically to preventing homelessness.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(9) A proposal for state resources and actions to prevent homelessness in addition to those described in paragraph (8).</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(10) Statewide homelessness
						prevention goals and accountability measures.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(11) An annual agenda recommending third-party evaluations of selected local or state homelessness prevention programs other than the homelessness prevention action plans that test the impact of those programs on homelessness prevention.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(12) Evidence-based model homelessness prevention practices identified or designed and developed by the<font color="#B30000"><strike> department</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> council</i></font> that include, but are not limited to, all of the following:</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(A) Identification of persons most at risk of homelessness through evidence-based risk
						factors, including, but not limited to, all of the following:</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 4em;">(i) Prior experience of homelessness.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 4em;">(ii) Annual income below 30 percent of the area median income.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 4em;">(iii) Rent burden.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 4em;">(iv) Other household and social characteristics that are known to elevate the risk of homelessness.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(B) The use of predictive models to identify individuals most at risk of homelessness.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(C) The targeting of resources to households most at risk of homelessness.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(D) The most effective and efficient
						interventions to prevent homelessness, including, but not limited to, all of the following:</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 4em;">(i) Financial assistance to increase housing stability, including, but not limited to, the most effective methods of accelerating the delivery of emergency rental assistance.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 4em;">(ii) Eviction defense and holistic legal services to increase housing stability.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 4em;">(iii) Case management to increase housing stability.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(E) Specific homelessness prevention practices that address the needs of subpopulations.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(F) Successful integration of financial, legal, and case management assistance.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(G) Evaluation of the effectiveness of homelessness prevention strategies on preventing homelessness, including performance metrics.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(H) The most effective and efficient means of coordinating state and federal homelessness prevention efforts identified and proposed by the<font color="#B30000"><strike> department.</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> council.</i></font></div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(I) The most effective and efficient means of coordinating state and local homeless prevention efforts identified and proposed by the<font color="#B30000"><strike> department.</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>
						council.</i></font></div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(J) Evidence-based state and local homelessness prevention programs and systems that have received evaluations validating their effectiveness in preventing homelessness identified by the<font color="#B30000"><strike> department</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> council</i></font> and recommendations for scaling up those programs and systems to have a broader impact on homelessness prevention.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(K) The compilation, acquisition, and use of relevant data necessary to effectuate homelessness prevention, including, but not limited to, a universal system of data collection and reporting that facilitates access to data by all participants in a
						homelessness prevention system.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(c) The<font color="#B30000"><strike> department</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>
						council</i></font>
						shall do both of the following with the model homelessness prevention practices described in paragraph (12) of subdivision (b):</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(1) Offer them as guidance to local programs.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(2) Propose methods to integrate relevant practices into state agencies and programs.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(d) The<font color="#B30000"><strike> department</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> council</i></font> shall annually review and update the strategy and publish any revisions.</div></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></body></html>
